{
  "texts": [
    "In order to achieve high performance, we adopt the emerging SNNversion BPTT learning algorithm 33 and extend it from ordinary SNNs to our DH-SNNs.",
    "The model parameters including synaptic weights, W, U, and timing factors, α, β, are automatically learned during training.",
    "Assuming the loss function is L and applying the chain rule of the gradient descent, the BPTT for the DH-SNN can follow",
    "where δ denotes the gradient of the loss function L with respect to specific variables.",
    "Note that H 0 actually does not exist due to the nondifferentiable spiking activities."
  ]
}